%I A390815 #21 Mar 06 2026 14:52:15
%S A390815 3,2,7,13,31,31,127,307,1093,1723,2801,3541,8191,5113,8011,10303,
%T A390815 19531,17293,28057,30941,30103,131071,88741,86143,147073,524287,
%U A390815 292561,459007,492103,797161,552793,579883,598303,684757,704761,732541,735307,830833,1191373
%N A390815 Denominators > 1 of ratio n!/sigma(n), where n! = factorial of n (A000142) and sigma(n) = sum of divisors of n (A000203).
%C A390815 First fractions n!/sigma(n) in their reduced form are: 2/3, 3/2, 24/7, 362880/13, 20922789888000/31, 15511210043330985984000000/31...
%C A390815 Conjecture: all terms are prime (verified for n <= 10^5).
%C A390815 Conjecture: for n >= 4 if sigma(n) does not divide n!, then n is a square. (verified for n <= 10^5).
%C A390815 See also comment in A390836 (numerators).
%C A390815 Is this the same as A062700 from the 3rd term on? - _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 06 2026
%e A390815 For n = 9, 9!/sigma(9) = 362880/13 and 13 does not divide 362880, so 13 is a term.
%e A390815 For n = 12, 12!/sigma(12) = 479001600/28 and 28 divides 479001600, so 28 is not a term.
%o A390815 (PARI) isok(n) = ((n! % sigma(n)) != 0); \\ A325436.
%o A390815 for(n=1,1000,if(isok(n),print1(denominator(n!/sigma(n))", ")))
%Y A390815 Cf. A000142, A000203.
%Y A390815 Cf. A325436, A390836.
%K A390815 nonn,frac,changed
%O A390815 1,1
%A A390815 _Claude H. R. Dequatre_, Feb 17 2026
